message:
Hi. Great post! I'm using AsyncLazy<t> for property caching, just like you described. But I also need to reset the property value, and I've not seen anything in the class for that (BTW, it's the same for Lazy<t>, there are ways but it would also be practical...).

Anyway I've added a Reset() method that just does  
 _mutex = new object();  
 _instance = new Lazy<task<t>>(_factory);

but I'm wondering if that method itself shouldn't be locked (using another object than _mutex?)?  
Thanks again!
